text: Baelor: I know we have been working hard these past weeks, and I want you to know I appreciate you all.
Rotta: What’s been the point? My clan won’t come out of their holes, they’re too busy forging armor too heavy to wear.
Osseus: And my fellow bone brethren won’t come to our aid either, they’re too obsessed with trying to repair themselves.
Gobkin: We change der minds, prrpppt. Rawrrr!
Rotta: How? With your little rusty kitchen knife?
Osseus: Perhaps his scintillating wit?
Baelor: Rotta, Osseus, Enough! Have I taught you nothing!? Osseus, you were cast out of your dungeon because they thought you too damaged, missing too many bones.
Osseus: Not THAT many! I mean nothing important! What do I need ribs for? It’s not like I have a heart left to protect!

Baelor: And Rotta, you were exiled for trying to bring new ideas to your clan. Just as I’m trying to do for Dungeons Incorporated!
I told them that if we use kindness and words to breed cooperation, instead of whips and chains to force subservience, we can build a better dungeon.
But because I am just an old man, and not a pulsating, undulating horror, I was dismissed.
So please, do not fall into the same trap as them.
Rotta: But look at it, it’s just so… small and helpless.
Osseus: And annoying…

Baelor: What does cruelty beget but more cruelty? Please, we must all cooperate if we are to survive.
Do not listen to their words, Gobkin, listen to your heart.
For that is your strength, and I sense that it will become more important than anything else in this entire dungeon.
Gobkin: Twuly!?

Baelor: Twuly! Uh, truely.
Now, we must gather the rats and skeletons to us, but before we embark, let’s go through our drills one last time.
Baelor: Remember to move together as one! Do not let foolhardy adventures divide you!
Rotta: I know how to walk…
Osseus: Well, scurry anyway…
Rotta: What was that!?
Osseus: Oh, Nothing…

Baelor: In battle, remember that brute force is not what wins.
It’s choosing the appropriate strategy for your opponent.
Gobkin, why don’t you start. Pick someone to fight first!
Gobkin: Oy, boney fwend! Come fights me!
Osseus: OW! MY SHIN!
Gobkin: Oh no! I’m sowry! You’se okays?
Osseus: HA FOOLED YOU!
Osseus: Heeeyah!
Osseus: Wo-WOAH!
Osseus: OH NO!

Rotta: I have some notes on your fighting style there Osseus.
Have you considered simply throwing your bones at the enemy?
Osseus: Nonsense, I just need to pick myself up…
Osseus: There, good as new.
Gobkin: Oy, Fur Fwend! Come make hits wid me!
Rotta: It’s Rotta. R-O-T-T-A.
Gobkin: That’s what I said! Fur fwend!
Rotta: Oh by my tail… just come on already! And…is that a cheese knife?
Gobkin: Yeh, yeh, knife, stabby stab.
Rotta: You know what, never mind, have at me!
Rotta: Oh that knife smells sweet… what is that? Hard cheddar? A hint of hickory?
Rotta: No, no focus! ARRGGGGHH!
Gobkin: AIEEEGGHHH!
Baelor: Well, fighting skill isn’t everything, and we won’t need to fight the rats or skeletons.
Rotta: You really think my people won’t fight you tooth and tail?
Osseus: And bone and… well bone, I suppose.
Baelor: Perhaps, but I also have this!
Baelor: The D20 of the Dungeon Master, given to all dungeon masters. With this, we will have unity.
Rotta: Ooooohhh...So green.
Osseus: Such fine craftsmanship.
Gobkin: It’s warm…
Baelor: Come, let’s begin our journey and I shall tell you how it functions…
Hero: En garde foul denizens of evil! I have come forth to smote thee!
Osseus: I heard that adventurers were pretentious but wow… to have a tongue and waste it so…
Rotta: ARRGGHHH! LET ME AT HIM!
Baelor: WAIT!
Baelor: NO! STOP, PLEASE!

Hero: I thought the Dungeon Guide listed this dungeon as a 2.5 stars?
Huh, I expected more challenge than this. Guess I’m better than I thought.

Hero: I have lay thee low, abominations, but harken! Ye have earned a reprieve for now!
I shall return in three days with other holy warriors and we shall purge your filth from these lands!

Hero: Man, these guys don’t even qualify as trash mobs.
However my low level friends will be able to grind xp quite easily in here!
Gobkin: M-m-master?
Baelor: I’m sorry. I thought I had more time.
Rotta: We-we-we have to stop the bleeding!
Osseus: The wound is too deep…

Baelor: Come closer Gobkin.
It’s up to you now, my boy. Take this. Use it. You’ll learn how.
You are the dungeon master now. Remember what I taught you, lead with compassion, not cruelty. Take care of them.
I wasn’t ready… there was so much to do.
Be good to each other… Make this dungeon a home…
Rotta: Now what do we do?
Osseus: We carry on! As we always have!

Rotta: Well we’ve always had a dungeon master too!
You can’t have a dungeon without a dungeon master!
Gobkin: I…I dunwon master.
Rotta: He was dying! He wasn’t thinking straight. Give me that, I’ll –
Rotta: What…?
Osseus: Seems he is indeed the dungeon master.
Rotta: Then we’re doomed.

Osseus: Perhaps, but, we’re doomed anyway. Shouldn’t we at least try?
Or would you prefer to just lay down and die?

Rotta: Never!
Where to Gobkin!?
